<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; SELF PRESERVATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL PLASCHKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The last time Italy played an Eastern European country in a World Cup game 
this big, it defeated Hungary for the 1938 championship, 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Afterward, Hungarian goalkeeper Antal Szabo said, "I have never felt so proud 
in my life. We may have lost the match, but we have saved 11 lives. The Italian 
players received a telegram from Rome before the game which read, 'Win or die.' 
Now they can go home heroes." 
</P>
<P>
 That telegram was reportedly sent by Italian dictator Benito Mussolini. BILL 
PLASCHKE 
</P>
</TEXT>
