<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; SOUNDS OF SILENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Not surprisingly, the best thing about the World Cup for the Swedes is that is 
has been quiet. 
</P>
<P>
 "For me, it has been perfect," Coach Tommy Svensson said. "It has been a good 
atmosphere at the games. Many matches have been very spectacular, with a lot of 
scoring. Outside (the stadiums), I don't think it has been that hysterical, as 
it can be in Spain, in Italy." RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
