WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; RAIDERS OF SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON HARRIS, Times Rio de Janeiro Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The main headline read: "Brazil Gets Ready to Suffocate the Swedes."And under 
another headline, "Bulgaria: Sex, Cigarettes and Sometimes Football," Jorge 
Luiz Rodrigues wrote in O Globo in Rio de Janeiro: 
</P>
<P>
 "They love parties, long nights and shopping. Most drink and smoke. And, once 
in a while, they practice." 
</P>
