<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; DOCTOR'S ORDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLIAM TUOHY, Times London Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several British papers reported the following: 
</P>
<P>
 A Kenyan witch doctor, who months ago supposedly forecast that Germany would 
lose in the quarterfinals, has predicted Brazilian success in the final. 
</P>
<P>
 Shariff Abubakar Omar told Kenyan reporters in Nairobi that he had written 
German Coach Berti Vogts that his team should seek mystical assistance, but 
received no reply. 
</P>
<P>
 "They have paid the price for ignoring my advice," he said. "The Germans would 
have made progress had they seen me. They needed the services of a magician." 
</P>
