<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; ITALY 1, BRAZIL 0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Italy has already won this World Cup -- at least the software version. 
</P>
<P>
 A World Cup simulation -- FIFA International Soccer -- was played this week 
and Italy defeated Brazil, 1-0, after 86 minutes without a goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Showing that video games are as fallible as, well, sportswriters, the other 
semifinalists were Germany and Spain. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was developed by EA Sports, an entertainment and educational San 
Mateo-based company. LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
