<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: BASS ACTION UNAFFECTED BY THE HEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some things never change . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Trout fisheries might be suffering because of the heat, and catfish fisheries 
might be coming on for the same reason, but the Southland's two primary bass 
fisheries seem unfazed by the weather. 
</P>
<P>
 Andy Andrews of Oxnard showed it is as easy to land a trophy-sized bass as it 
was in early spring at Lake Casitas, pulling a 10-pound 3-ounce bass and 
another 7-12 fish out of the Ventura County reservoir. Mike Carpenter of Canyon 
Country made it look even easier at Castaic Lake, landing three fish over the 
10-pound mark, none at 12-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
