NEWSWIRE: GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jenny Lee of Fullerton shot two-over-par 75 and lost medalist honors by one 
stroke to Kelli Kuehne of McKinney, Tex., at the U.S. Girls' Junior Golf 
Championship in Great Falls, Mont. Lee, who shot a tournament-record 67 Monday, 
finished at four-under 142 and will be seeded second in match play that starts 
today.Jenny Glasgow of Corona del Mar shot 74 to finish stroke play at 153 to 
easily make the cut. Jane Park of Buena Park had 162 and won a playoff for one 
of the final spots. 
</P>
<P>
 In the U.S. Amateur Public Links Championship, Kevin Claborn of Brea shot a 
one-under 71 and made the cut by one stroke for match play in Bigfork, Mont. 
Claborn finished with a two-day total of 148. . . . In the American Junior Golf 
Assn. Rolex Tournament of Champions in Edmond, Okla., Fullerton's Terry Noe 
shot two-over 74 and is six strokes behind the leader. In the girls' division, 
Alicia Allison of Santa Ana shot 76 and is in a tie for third, three shots 
behind the leader. Kellee Booth of Coto de Caza shot 80. 
</P>
