<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Mimi Ko, RIO MAGALH; Cathy Curtis 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FRONT-ROW SEAT: Chris Bancroft of Anaheim was well aware how many millions 
were watching the O.J. Simpson preliminary hearing last week -- they were 
watching it through his camera. . . . Bancroft, 31, a graduate of Magnolia High 
School and Cal State Fullerton, operated the courtroom camera -- and decided 
the angles -- for Court TV. Says Bancroft: "I covered the Menendez trial, and I 
thought that was a big deal. But this was a big deal. I could feel the 
responsibility. Fortunately, from the responses we got, I guess I did OK." 
</P>
<P>
 NOT A BESTSELLER? Galal Kernahan of Laguna Hills Leisure World recently sent a 
postcard to the state's Legislative Bill Room, requesting a current copy of the 
California Constitution. It was returned with this message: "Out of Print.". . 
. . "I find it disturbing that the state is operating without its owner's 
manual," Kernahan joked. The Bill Room does have copies now, or you can get one 
from the secretary of state's office. 
</P>
<P>
 MIKE SCHOOL: ESPN's Roy Firestone has had numerous accolades heaped upon him 
as a top TV sports interviewer. So when he agreed to teach a session on 
broadcasting skills in the annual Sportscaster camp run by Roy Englebrecht, 
above, Firestone's topic, of course, was interviewing. The camp -- 
Englebrecht's 10th annual -- opens today at the Radisson Plaza Hotel in Irvine 
and runs through Sunday. One of its 100 participants: former NBA star Walter 
Davis, who's preparing for a broadcast career. 
</P>
<P>
 STILL AT IT: If you've ever taken a tourist bus in Washington, D.C., one of 
the stops is the famous monument "Flag Raising on Iwo Jima," just across the 
Potomac River in Arlington, Va. The 78-foot-high sculpture is the most famous 
of 1,200 commissioned pieces by Felix de Weldon. Close friend Ellen Turnbull of 
Laguna Niguel says of Weldon, now 77, "He's still sculpting!" And reminiscing. 
. . . The artist speaks this morning at the Monarch Beach Sunrise Rotary Club 
at a gathering arranged by Turnbull. 
</P>
