 THEY'RE OUT: There's no crying in baseball, but nobody said anything against 
folding. And that's exactly what an American Legion team in Newbury Park has 
done (C8). Two reasons: not enough players and not enough money. . . . 
Meanwhile, American Legion ball is a big deal in the San Fernando Valley. A 
team from Woodland Hills, in fact, won the World Series in 1989, with alum Ryan 
McGuire now playing in the Red Sox organization. 
</P>
