<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OFFICE AND COMPUTER TRAINING AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free computer, clerical and general office training is being offered by 
Goodwill Industries of Ventura and Santa Barbara counties through the 
organization's Oxnard facility, officials say.  
</P>
<P>
 Twelve full-time openings are currently available for people who want to learn 
how to operate a microcomputer and a variety of business software, according to 
Robert Dyer, unit director. 
</P>
<P>
 Dyer said the classes are open-ended with flexible scheduling, but that most 
students take about 90 days to become proficient with the machines and 
programs. Also included in the training are proper office organization, filing 
system techniques, telephone procedures and general business etiquette. 
</P>
<P>
 Goodwill's Oxnard training center is located at 350 Cactus Drive. Eligible 
students must be at least 18 years old and possess sixth-grade-level reading, 
language and math skills. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call 983-3414. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
