<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena city officials will begin settlement talks today with angry vendors 
at a Pasadena-backed soccer festival who are demanding that the city cover 
their losses from the monthlong event that has drawn small crowds and produced 
few sales. 
</P>
<P>
 Called Soccer Carnaval, the festival in Brookside Park near the Rose Bowl was 
supposed to combine soccer activities, crafts, entertainment, food and carnival 
rides. It was launched as a joint venture of the city and Pasadena Productions, 
