<TEXT>
<P>
 Nationwide Health Properties Inc.: The Newport Beach real estate investment 
trust said its profit for the second quarter rose 11% to $11.2 million, or 62 
cents a share, from $10.1 million, or 58 cents a share, for the same period a 
year earlier.Revenue increased 18% to $17.4 million from $14.7 million. For the 
first half, profit was up 13% to $22.2 million, or $1.22 a share, from $19.7 
million, or $1.14 a share, for the same period a year earlier. Six-month 
revenue rose 16% to $33.9 million from $29.2 million. 
</P>
