<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: THE ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Consumer Credit Up $10.4 Billion: Americans' credit card purchases increased 
for the 14th consecutive month in May, bringing installment credit to a 
seasonally adjusted $837.701 billion after an increase of $10.115 billion in 
April, the Federal Reserve said.The annual rate of borrowing was 15.1% in May, 
up from 14.9% in April. The figures are based on benchmark revisions on 
statistics from 1989 to 1994. Although monthly increases are larger than before 
as a result of the revisions, the trend in borrowing hasn't changed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
