National Real Estate Index said.But the gains continued to be chalked up mainly 
in western states outside California and in the economically strong Sun Belt 
states, led by a surge in apartment property values, the research firm said in 
its quarterly report. Saying the commercial real estate market "is back," 
National Real Estate said its composite price index increased 1.8% in the 
quarter. That follows a 1.1% gain in the previous quarter and marks the fourth 
consecutive quarter the index has risen. It gained 3.0% for the 12 months ended 
March 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
